<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-12T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-12T16:36:00-05:00" n="1280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/19</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-12T15:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>85. My telegram No. 81, April 11, 3 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d1280fn2">Not
                                printed.</note> I am informed that the Sonora authorities have been
                            ordered by telegraph to suspend proceedings as requested and to make a
                            report on the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>